[Palmerston North (https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palmerston_North) is a city located in the Manawatu-Whanganui region of the North Island of New Zealand, commonly referred to as Palmerston, or Palmy by locals. The initial outbreak of _S._ Typhi was in Aukland, on the north side of North Island.

As noted, in the posting, there is a connection between at least one of the children and the cluster in Aukland. The infection is transmitted primarily from person-to-person via contaminated water or food rather than direct spread although the childcare setting is problematic. - Mod.LL


